{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"stolen-flattering-hedgehog","description":"## Context\nThe first asymmetric scheme: sign/verify via OpenSSH `ssh-keygen -Y` (stdlib subprocess, no new core dep), against an allowed_signers-format trust input, reusing developers' SSH keys.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `src/rebar/attest/sshsig.py` signs/verifies via `ssh-keygen -Y` using argv arrays (no shell), branching only on exit code, allowlist-validating namespace + principal.\n- [ ] Test matrix asserts fail-closed on: tampered bytes, wrong namespace, unknown principal, substituted key, expired validity window.\n- [ ] `ssh-keygen` >=8.9 detected at startup; absence fails closed with a clear error (test asserts no silent pass).","id":"56d9-0869-428c-44a3","parent_id":"2fd4-baa0-4471-4382","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"attest: SSHSIG scheme via ssh-keygen (fail-closed subprocess)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783735856443512001,"uuid":"937f1c3e-64c8-411f-8194-e08d1ae6c60d"}